{"lemma":"عِلْكَةٍ","slug":"عِلْكَةٍ","root":"ع.ل.ك","root_slug":"ع-ل-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ل-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30323","n30330","n30331"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to chew, to knead with the teeth, to champ"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tighten the hands upon from stinginess, to manage strictly, to tend well"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to prattle, to blather"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fix or fasten with resin"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَلَكَ (ʕalaka) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"resin, mastix, gum, chewing gum and the like"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"viscose, glutinous, which can be chewed long, sticky and slimy","examples":[{"text":"إن أرض مصر رملية لا تصلح للزراعة، لكنه يأتيها طين أسود علك فيه دسومة كثيرة يسمى الإيليز؛ يأتيها من بلاد السودان مختلطًا بماء النيل عند مده، فيستقر الطين، وينضب الماء، فيحرث ويزرع. وكل سنة يأتيها طين جديد، ولهذا يزرع جميع أراضيها ولا يراح شيء منها، كما يفعل في العراق والشام.","english":"The land of Egypt is sandy and unsuitable for agriculture, but to it comes a black viscose mud of much richness called ʾiblīz; it comes from the lands of the Sudan mingled with Nile water at rising tide, and the mud having settled and the water having drained one can plough and sow. And every year new mud comes to it and most of the regions of Egypt are sown by this, and it wanes by no jot, unlike it does in Iraq or Syria."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30323","headword_ar":"عَلَكَهُ","root":"Elk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalokN","text_ar":"عَلْكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He chewed it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moved it backwards and forwards in his mouth, to chew it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealaka All~ijaAma","text_ar":"عَلَكَ اللِّجَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chewed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"champed, the bit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moved it about,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alakahu","text_ar":"اَلَكَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alk","text_ar":"الك"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealaka","text_ar":"عَلَكَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAbayohi","text_ar":"نَابَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grated, his canine teeth, one with the other, so that a sound was produced."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealakato EajiynahaA","text_ar":"عَلَكَتْ عَجِينَهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She kneaded well her dough."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","O"]},{"entry_id":"n30330","headword_ar":"عَلَكَةٌ","root":"Elk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fat and goodly she-camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30331","headword_ar":"عَلِكَةٌ","root":"Elk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqo$iqap","text_ar":"شِقْشِقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faucial bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the camel, when he brays:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalikaAtN","text_ar":"عَلِكَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) ―         -b2-  And the latter, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalikaAtN","text_ar":"عَلِكَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong canine teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) this is said by some to be its meaning in a verse of Ru-beh. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}